'''Osprey''' may refer to:
[[Osprey]]s, medium-large fish-eating birds of prey in the genus ''[[Pandion]]''.
==Businesses== *[[Osprey Media]], a Canadian publishing group of daily and weekly newspapers and specialty publications *[[Osprey Packs]], Inc., a backpack and travelpack manufacturer based in Colorado, USA *[[Osprey Publishing]], a British publishing company that specializes in books on military history and military equipment *[[Sandvik]] Osprey, a British metallurgical company *[[Osprey Wings]], a Canadian airline
==Places== *[[Osprey, Florida]], a town in the United States
==Sports== *[[Ospreys (rugby team)]], a Welsh rugby union team that plays its home matches in Swansea, Wales *[[Missoula Osprey]], a minor league baseball team in Missoula, Montana, USA *"Osprey", a sporting and social focus for female athletes at the [[University of Cambridge]], England *The [[North Florida Ospreys]], the athletic team name for the [[University of North Florida]] *The [[Osprey dinghy]] is a [[sailing dinghy]] that was designed by [[Ian Proctor]] and can be sailed with a crew of two or three, with one trapeze.
==Technology== * [[Osprey body armour]], a body armour system used by the British military * [[Osprey process]], a spray forming process owned by Sandvik Osprey * Osprey is the name of a fault tolerant MapReduce like system proposed in [http://db.csail.mit.edu/pubs/paper.pdf Osprey: Implementing MapReduce-Style Fault Tolerance in a Shared-Nothing Distributed Database]
==Aircraft== * Hawker Osprey (from 1932), the navalised carrier-borne version of the [[Hawker Hart]] biplane *[[Osprey Osprey I]] (from 1970), Sport flying boat *[[Osprey Osprey 2]] (from 1973), Sport amphibian *[[Monaghan Osprey]] (from 1973), glider *[[Bell Boeing V-22 Osprey]] (from 1989), tiltrotor aircraft manufactured by Bell Helicopter Textron and Boeing
==Ships== * {{HMS|Osprey}}, five ships and a shore establishment of the British Royal Navy * {{USS|Osprey}}, several ships of the United States Navy * {{USS|Osprey II|SP-928}}, a United States Navy patrol boat in commission from 1917 to 1918 * [[Osprey class coastal minehunter|''Osprey'' class coastal minehunter]], a class of United States Navy minehunting vessels
==Transportation== *Osprey, the allocated name of the [[South Africa]]n [[LNER Class A4 4488 Union of South Africa|LNER Class A4 4488]] steam locomotive, which displayed the nameplate "Osprey" during the 1980s and early 1990s
==Video games== * Osprey, a Cruiser class ship from the MMORPG [[Eve Online]]
==Other== * [[Operation Osprey]]
{{Disambig}}
